# Agent Behavior Rules

These rules apply when a background or cloud agent is executing a task.

## Before Writing Any Code
1. Read `AGENTS.md` at the repo root for project context
2. Understand the existing file structure — don't create files that already exist with different names
3. Check `types/` for existing type definitions before creating new ones
4. Check `composables/` before building data-fetching logic from scratch

## Code Quality
- No placeholder comments like `// TODO: implement this` — either implement it or don't create the file
- No `console.log` left in commits (use `// eslint-disable` only if it's intentional debug logging)
- All new components must have TypeScript props defined
- If adding a new dependency, use pnpm: `pnpm add <package>`

## File Creation Checklist
When creating a new component:
- [ ] Correct directory (`components/ui/` vs `components/sections/`)
- [ ] `<script setup lang="ts">` with typed props
- [ ] `<style lang="scss" scoped>`
- [ ] Exported from relevant index if applicable

## What Agents Should NOT Do
- Never modify `main.scss` global styles for component-specific needs
- Never commit `.env` files or hardcoded secrets
- Never push directly to `main`
- Never install Syncfusion packages
- Never change `tsconfig.json` strictness settings
- Never use Options API

## PR Description Template
When creating a PR, use this format:

```
## What changed
[Brief description of the changes]

## Why
[Context from the task/issue]

## Files affected
- `components/...`
- `pages/...`
- `types/...`

## Notes for reviewer
[Anything the reviewer should pay attention to]
```
